#: ajdg-matomo-tracker-dashboard.php:53
msgid "Monitor 404 pages:"
msgstr ""

#: ajdg-matomo-tracker-dashboard.php:57
msgid ""
"Monitor which urls redirect to a 404 error page. Discover which page the "
"visitor tried to reach and where they came from."
msgstr ""

#: ajdg-matomo-tracker-dashboard.php:57
msgid ""
"Look for \"404/URL\" items in the Behaviour > Page Titles section. This can "
"help you find and fix old/invalid urls."
msgstr ""

#: ajdg-matomo-tracker-dashboard.php:59
msgid "Record feed clickthrough:"
msgstr ""

#: ajdg-matomo-tracker-dashboard.php:63
msgid ""
"Record when visitors click through to your website from your RSS and Atom "
"feeds."
msgstr ""

#: ajdg-matomo-tracker-dashboard.php:63
msgid ""
"Look for the \"feed_click\" campaign in Acquisition > Campaigns. Includes a "
"basic bot filter."
msgstr ""

#: ajdg-matomo-tracker-dashboard.php:65
msgid "Track downloads in WooCommerce:"
msgstr ""

#: ajdg-matomo-tracker-dashboard.php:69
msgid ""
"Tracks downloads for WooCommerce downloadable products that get downloaded "
"via the users account/dashboard."
msgstr ""

#: ajdg-matomo-tracker-dashboard.php:69
msgid ""
"Downloads show up in Behavior > Downloads. The url is unformatted because "
"WooCommerce does not provide a way to do so."
msgstr ""

#: ajdg-matomo-tracker-dashboard.php:75
msgid "Privacy options"
msgstr ""

#: ajdg-matomo-tracker-dashboard.php:78
msgid "Respect DoNotTrack:"
msgstr ""

#: ajdg-matomo-tracker-dashboard.php:82
msgid ""
"Do not track visitors who sent a DoNotTrack request (incognito mode). "
"Setting this to \"Yes\" will respect DoNotTrack requests but results in less "
"accurate stats. Selecting \"No\" may break some (unenforceable) privacy laws "
"in certain countries. If you choose to ignore DoNotTrack, you may want to "
"anonymize the recorded data in your Matomo settings as a courtesy."
msgstr ""

#: ajdg-matomo-tracker-dashboard.php:84
msgid "Track time on site:"
msgstr ""

#: ajdg-matomo-tracker-dashboard.php:88
msgid ""
"Periodically check on visitors to see if they are still there. This results "
"in time visitors spent on pages is recorded with greater accuracy. Time "
"spent on pages is visible on many dashboards throughout Matomo."
msgstr ""

#: ajdg-matomo-tracker-dashboard.php:94
msgid "Advanced options"
msgstr ""

#: ajdg-matomo-tracker-dashboard.php:97
msgid "You probably do <u>not</u> need these."
msgstr ""

#: ajdg-matomo-tracker-dashboard.php:99
msgid "Record feed views:"
msgstr ""

#: ajdg-matomo-tracker-dashboard.php:103
msgid ""
"Record when readers view your posts through your RSS and Atom feeds. "
"Pageviews are counted as regular pageviews and as a campaign named "
"\"feed_impression\" in Acquisition > Campaigns. Includes a basic bot filter. "
"Does not track excerpts."
msgstr ""

#: ajdg-matomo-tracker-dashboard.php:103
msgid "<b>Caution:</b> Using this feature may offset your pageviews."
msgstr ""

#: ajdg-matomo-tracker-dashboard.php:105
msgid "Track in high accuracy mode:"
msgstr ""

#: ajdg-matomo-tracker-dashboard.php:109
msgid ""
"Track in a fast polling mode for higher accuracy for certain stats. This is "
"useful if your outbound clicks and similar stats seem inconclusive."
msgstr ""

#: ajdg-matomo-tracker-dashboard.php:109
msgid ""
"<b>Caution:</b> Using this feature may increase CPU usage on the visitors "
"browser and on your server."
msgstr ""

